---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const faqQuestions = [
  {
    question: "Can I move plants interstate in Australia?",
    answer: "Yes, most common house plants can be moved interstate. However, some states have quarantine restrictions. We recommend checking with your state's biosecurity department for specific rules."
  },
  {
    question: "How do I prepare pot plants for interstate transport?",
    answer: "Water plants 2-3 days before moving (not the day before), prune any dead leaves, wrap delicate plants in paper, and for fragile pots, consider repotting into plastic containers temporarily."
  },
  {
    question: "Will my plants survive an interstate move?",
    answer: "Most hardy plants survive well. Succulents, ferns, and established pot plants typically handle 2-5 day transits without issues. Avoid moving plants in extreme heat."
  },
  {
    question: "What plants can't be moved interstate?",
    answer: "Fruit trees, some palms, and plants with soil from certain regions may be restricted. Western Australia and Tasmania have stricter rules. Always check the destination state's quarantine requirements."
  }
];
---

<Layout 
  title="Moving Pot Plants Interstate | How to Transport Plants Safely | Moving Again"
  description="Complete guide to moving pot plants interstate in Australia. Learn how to prepare, pack, and transport your plants safely across state lines."
  schemaType="FAQPage"
  schemaData={{ questions: faqQuestions }}
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-800 to-green-900 text-white py-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
        <span class="inline-block px-4 py-1 mb-6 rounded-full bg-green-500/20 text-green-300 font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-sm">
          Plant Moving Guide
        </span>
        
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black mb-6">
          Moving Pot Plants Interstate
        </h1>
        
        <p class="text-xl text-green-100 mb-8">
          Everything you need to know about transporting your beloved plants safely across Australia.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <article class="py-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-lg">
        
        <h2>Can You Move Plants Interstate?</h2>
        <p>
          Yes! Moving pot plants interstate is absolutely possible, but there are a few things you need to know. Each Australian state has different quarantine rules, and proper preparation can mean the difference between thriving plants and sad, droopy ones. If you're planning an <a href="/moving-interstate/" class="text-brand-red hover:underline">interstate move</a>, your plants can come too—with the right care.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-400 p-6 my-8 not-prose rounded-r-lg">
          <p class="font-bold text-yellow-800 mb-2">⚠️ Important: State Quarantine Rules</p>
          <p class="text-yellow-700">
            Western Australia and Tasmania have strict biosecurity rules. Some plants, especially those with soil, may need inspection or may not be allowed. Check your destination state's requirements before moving.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2>How to Prepare Your Plants for Moving</h2>
        
        <h3>1-2 Weeks Before the Move</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Prune back:</strong> Remove dead leaves, long branches, and any dying foliage</li>
          <li><strong>Treat pests:</strong> Check for insects and treat if necessary—you don't want to transport pests</li>
          <li><strong>Consider repotting:</strong> Move fragile ceramic pots into lightweight plastic containers</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2-3 Days Before the Move</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Water thoroughly:</strong> Give plants a good drink, but not on moving day (wet soil is heavy and messy)</li>
          <li><strong>Remove saucers:</strong> Take off drainage saucers and any decorative pot covers</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Moving Day</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Wrap delicate plants:</strong> Use paper or cotton sheets (avoid plastic—plants need to breathe)</li>
          <li><strong>Secure pots:</strong> Place in boxes with newspaper padding to prevent tipping</li>
          <li><strong>Keep upright:</strong> Plants should always travel standing up, not on their side</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What Plants Travel Best?</h2>
        
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8 not-prose">
          <div class="bg-green-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-3">✅ Great Travelers</h3>
            <ul class="text-green-700 space-y-2">
              <li>• Succulents & cacti</li>
              <li>• Snake plants</li>
              <li>• Pothos & philodendrons</li>
              <li>• ZZ plants</li>
              <li>• Spider plants</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-red-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-red-800 mb-3">⚠️ Need Extra Care</h3>
            <ul class="text-red-700 space-y-2">
              <li>• Fiddle leaf figs (drama queens!)</li>
              <li>• Orchids</li>
              <li>• Large palms</li>
              <li>• Flowering plants</li>
              <li>• Ferns (sensitive to dry air)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2>Interstate Quarantine Guide</h2>
        
        <p>
          Australia takes biosecurity seriously. Here's a quick guide by state:
        </p>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto my-8 not-prose">
          <table class="w-full border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-brand-dark text-white">
                <th class="p-3 text-left">State</th>
                <th class="p-3 text-left">Strictness</th>
                <th class="p-3 text-left">Key Rules</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y">
              <tr>
                <td class="p-3 font-medium">Western Australia</td>
                <td class="p-3"><span class="text-red-500 font-bold">STRICT</span></td>
                <td class="p-3">Most plants require inspection. No fruit plants.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="p-3 font-medium">Tasmania</td>
                <td class="p-3"><span class="text-red-500 font-bold">STRICT</span></td>
                <td class="p-3">Quarantine at border. Many soil restrictions.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="p-3 font-medium">South Australia</td>
                <td class="p-3"><span class="text-yellow-500 font-bold">MODERATE</span></td>
                <td class="p-3">Some fruit tree restrictions.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="p-3 font-medium">NSW, VIC, QLD</td>
                <td class="p-3"><span class="text-green-500 font-bold">RELAXED</span></td>
                <td class="p-3">Most house plants allowed. Check for pests.</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h2>Can Moving Again Transport My Plants?</h2>
        
        <p>
          We can transport pot plants as part of your <a href="/backloading/" class="text-brand-red hover:underline">backloading service</a>. Here's what you need to know:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>Plants must be properly prepared and wrapped</li>
          <li>We recommend hardy varieties for longer transits</li>
          <li>You're responsible for meeting quarantine requirements</li>
          <li>Plants travel at owner's risk (they're living things!)</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="bg-brand-red/5 border border-brand-red/20 p-6 my-8 rounded-xl not-prose text-center">
          <p class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-dark mb-4">
            Planning an interstate move with plants?
          </p>
          <a 
            href="https://removalistquotes.movingagain.com.au/quote/household" 
            class="inline-block py-3 px-8 bg-brand-red text-white font-bold rounded-brand hover:bg-brand-accent transition-colors"
          >
            Get a Free Quote
          </a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center text-brand-dark mb-12">
        Frequently Asked Questions
      </h2>
      
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-4">
        {faqQuestions.map((faq) => (
          <details class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 group">
            <summary class="p-6 cursor-pointer font-bold text-brand-dark flex justify-between items-center">
              {faq.question}
              <span class="text-brand-red group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600">
              {faq.answer}
            </div>
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
